			<text>
			<![CDATA[<textformat leading="12"><font size="17"></font><br><br><font size="14">All seafarers must be conscious of the pollution threats to waterways and oceans and the serious effects that may result.<br><br>MARPOL covers accidental and operational oil pollution as well as pollution by chemicals, goods in packaged form, sewage, garbage and air pollution.<br><br>The IMO’s Intervention Convention affirms the right of coastal states to take measures on the high seas to prevent, mitigate or eliminate dangers to their coastlines from marine casualties.</font></textformat>]]>
			</text>
