			<![CDATA[<textformat leading="12"><font size="14"></font><br><br><font size="14">The International Convention on Oil Pollution Preparedness, Response and Co-operation (OPRC) provides a global framework for international co-operation in combating major incidents or threats of marine pollution. A protocol to this convention covers marine pollution by hazardous and noxious substances (HNS).<br><br>The Marine Environment Protection Committee (MEPC) is IMO’s senior technical body on marine pollution related matters. This Committee is aided in its work by a number of Sub-Committees.</font></textformat>]]>
